WITH filtered AS (
  SELECT
    tenant_id,
    chain_id,
    `timestamp`,
    role
  FROM "liveassist_chat"."chat_messages"
  WHERE
    $__timeFilter(`timestamp`)
    AND role IN ('user', 'assistant')         -- only roles we care about
),
sorted AS (
  SELECT
    chain_id,
    -- Array of tuples (ts, role) sorted by timestamp
    arraySort(groupArray(tuple(`timestamp`, role))) AS evts
  FROM filtered
  GROUP BY chain_id
)
SELECT
  pair.2.1 AS time,                                   -- assistant msg timestamp
  dateDiff('second', pair.1.1, pair.2.1) AS value,    -- response time in seconds
  chain_id AS metric
FROM
(
  SELECT
    chain_id,
    arrayJoin(
      arrayZip(
        arrayPopBack(evts),    -- previous (ts, role)
        arrayPopFront(evts)    -- current  (ts, role)
      )
    ) AS pair
  FROM sorted
)
WHERE pair.1.2 = 'user' AND pair.2.2 = 'assistant'    -- user → assistant only
ORDER BY time
LIMIT 1000;

targets.rawQuery:
SELECT 
    ApplicationName,
    d.name AS Dscp,
    SUM(SumOctets)/5 AS TotalBytes,
    SUM(SumFlowCount) AS TotalFlows,
    SUM(SumPackets)/5 AS TotalPackets,
    SUM(SumOctets)*8/5/60 AS AverageBitRate,
    AVG(SumPackets)/5/60 AS AveragePacketRate,
    MAX(SumOctets)*8/5/60 AS PeakBitRate,
    MAX(SumPackets)/5/60 AS PeakPacketRate
FROM livenx_flowdb.basic_entity_app_5m_dist as f
JOIN livenx_flowdb.dscp AS d ON toUInt8(f.Dscp) = d.dscp
WHERE
    time >= 1708095989 AND time <= 1708096889 AND 
    (('All' LIKE 'All') OR (ApplicationName LIKE 'All')) AND 
    (('All' LIKE 'All') OR (d.name LIKE 'All')) AND  
    (('All' LIKE 'All') OR (DeviceSerial LIKE 'All'))
GROUP BY ApplicationName, Dscp
LIMIT 1000

/* SNMP inBytes counter → BYTES/SEC (no window funcs, sorted by time ASC) */
WITH base AS (
  SELECT
    DeviceId,
    Tags['description'] AS Memory,
    time,
    ifNull(AVG(MetricValue), 0.) AS v                 -- ensure non-null
  FROM livenx_snmpdb.device_metric_dist
  WHERE MetricName LIKE '%emory%'
    AND $__timeFilter(time)
  GROUP BY
    DeviceId, Memory, time
),
agg AS (
  SELECT
    DeviceId,
    Memory,
    /* sort (time,value) tuples by time */
    arraySort(x -> x.1, groupArray( (time, v) )) AS tv,
    arrayMap(x -> x.1, tv) AS times,
    arrayMap(x -> ifNull(x.2, 0.), tv) AS vals,          -- Array(Float64)
    arrayDifference(vals) AS diffs,                      -- first element = 0
    /* seconds between samples (same length as times/vals) */
    arrayDifference(arrayMap(x -> toUnixTimestamp(x.1), tv)) AS dt
  FROM base
  GROUP BY
    DeviceId, Memory
),
flat AS (
  SELECT
    DeviceId,
    Memory,
    /* drop the synthetic first delta with arraySlice(..., 2) */
    arraySlice(times, 2) AS t_arr,
    arraySlice(diffs, 2) AS d_arr,
    arraySlice(dt, 2)    AS s_arr
  FROM agg
)
SELECT
  t AS time,
  DeviceId,
  Memory,
  /* clip negatives from resets; for wrap handling use IF(d < 0, d + 4294967296, d) for 32-bit, or + 18446744073709551616 for 64-bit */
  if(secs > 0, greatest(d, 0) / secs, 0) AS Mem
FROM flat
ARRAY JOIN
  t_arr AS t,
  d_arr AS d,
  s_arr AS secs
/* Strict global sort so the consumer sees ascending time */
ORDER BY time ASC, DeviceId, Memory;

/* SNMP inBytes counter → BYTES/SEC (no window funcs, sorted by time ASC) */
WITH base AS (
  SELECT
    DeviceId,
    Tags['description'] AS CPU,
    time,
    ifNull(AVG(MetricValue), 0.) AS v                 -- ensure non-null
  FROM livenx_snmpdb.device_metric_dist
  WHERE MetricName LIKE '%cpu%'
    AND $__timeFilter(time)
  GROUP BY
    DeviceId, CPU, time
),
agg AS (

    arrayMap(x -> x.1, tv) AS times,
    arrayMap(x -> ifNull(x.2, 0.), tv) AS vals,          -- Array(Float64)
    arrayDifference(vals) AS diffs,                      -- first element = 0
    /* seconds between samples (same length as times/vals) */
    arrayDifference(arrayMap(x -> toUnixTimestamp(x.1), tv)) AS dt
  FROM base
  GROUP BY
    DeviceId, CPU
),
flat AS (
  SELECT
    DeviceId,
    CPU,
    /* drop the synthetic first delta with arraySlice(..., 2) */
    arraySlice(times, 2) AS t_arr,
    arraySlice(diffs, 2) AS d_arr,

  FROM agg
)

ORDER BY time ASC, DeviceId, CPU;
